{"TopicId":139024,"ForumId":34,"TopicTitle":"[1.10.x] EasyBoard v1.10 : Board key works as a toggle","CreatedByName":"Dizor","CreatedById":161502,"CreatedDateTime":"2016-05-05T09:26:04Z","PageNum":5,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Tallinu","CreatedById":57810,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-30T11:05:15Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAh, thanks!\u00A0I think the wording of \u0022non-resettable\u0022 must be what confused me -- as in,\u00A0\u0022But why can\u0027t I reset it? How is that a good thing?\u0022 \u003Cimg alt=\u0022:D\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_cheesy.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:D\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI guess it really meant \u0022non-resetting\u0022 as in \u0022it doesn\u0027t get\u00A0reset when you switch away from them.\u0022 And the hotkey in #3 is just a way of setting more than one of them to do that en-masse.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dizor","CreatedById":161502,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-30T14:49:26Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223663369\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221567159220\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002257810\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Tallinu\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n4 hours ago, Tallinu said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSorry if I\u0027m being dense, but what does this mean?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nYou can set the intention to board (B) or to grab a ladder (F) as usual, for example for Jeb, and then switch to another kerbal or vessel near to Jeb and do whatever you want. Jeb will remember what to do. The intention will only be reset when you reload the game scene (e.g. load saved game, or switch to another distant vessel on map).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beetlecat","CreatedById":92207,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-08-30T17:14:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223661387\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221566941327\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022161502\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Dizor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 8/27/2019 at 2:28 PM, Dizor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022129964\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/129964-linuxgurugamer/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@linuxgurugamer\u003C/a\u003E, \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u002257176\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/57176-taniwha/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@taniwha\u003C/a\u003E,\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ENew version 1.8.1 is released.\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nUpdates:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1. Implemented non resettable independent kerbal intentions.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n2. Fixed camera jump-away-effect when boarding vessel (it would be good to zoom out camera a little for large vessels, but i don\u0027t know how to do it).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n3. Implemented the \u0022herd instinct\u0022 (mass kerbals intentions). Hotkeys: \u003Cstrong\u003ERightCtrl\u002BB\u003C/strong\u003E and \u003Cstrong\u003ERightCtrl\u002BF\u003C/strong\u003E.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis update allows you to collect kerbals like this:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022fKTeb8.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.33\u0022 height=\u0022338\u0022 width=\u0022600\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.vgy.me/fKTeb8.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGASP! This is fantastic!!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Crimor","CreatedById":18370,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-18T16:55:30Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes this work fine in 1.8.x? It\u0027s a mod that you can\u0027t live without once you start using it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Beetlecat","CreatedById":92207,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-11-18T17:39:31Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223706825\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221574096130\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002218370\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Crimor\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n43 minutes ago, Crimor said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDoes this work fine in 1.8.x? It\u0027s a mod that you can\u0027t live without once you start using it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s working -- / I\u0027m using it. No idea if needs a recompile, etc. but you should be good to go! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dizor","CreatedById":161502,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-01T16:10:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nRecompiled just in case (v1.8.2)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gordon Dry","CreatedById":163177,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-01T17:00:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022161502\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dizor\u003C/a\u003E thanks for the update - the previous version worked on KSP 1.8.1 btw\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I have a question, perhaps you can lead me to a solution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m just used to it that \u0022grab to a ladder\u0022 does not work for me for a long time now. Several KSP generations tbh.\u003Cbr\u003E\nLiterally, I\u0027m used to it that grabbing a ladder is not safe enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould it be that other mods like KJR or WorldStabilizer somehow interfere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs soon as the Kerbal grabbed a ladder or a handrail, he/she/it does not stick to that position but slides \u0022downwards\u0022 until he/she/it reaches the end of the ladder / handrail, then floats around (in space) or falls down (when landed).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo exception in the log at that time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gordon Dry","CreatedById":163177,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-02T13:07:52Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022161502\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dizor\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167015-whale_2/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167015\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167015-whale_2/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@whale_2\u003C/a\u003E I will do a test next session, I just add \u003Cem\u003EKerbalEVA\u003C/em\u003E to the \u003Cem\u003EexcludePartModules\u003C/em\u003E list.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dizor","CreatedById":161502,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-02T16:25:41Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223712152\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575219646\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gordon Dry\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n23 hours ago, Gordon Dry said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022161502\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dizor\u003C/a\u003E thanks for the update - the previous version worked on KSP 1.8.1 btw\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut I have a question, perhaps you can lead me to a solution.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027m just used to it that \u0022grab to a ladder\u0022 does not work for me for a long time now. Several KSP generations tbh.\u003Cbr\u003E\nLiterally, I\u0027m used to it that grabbing a ladder is not safe enough.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nCould it be that other mods like KJR or WorldStabilizer somehow interfere?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAs soon as the Kerbal grabbed a ladder or a handrail, he/she/it does not stick to that position but slides \u0022downwards\u0022 until he/she/it reaches the end of the ladder / handrail, then floats around (in space) or falls down (when landed).\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNo exception in the log at that time.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThis can happen in case your craft have some acceleration/deceleration, or it is just moving through atmosphere and wind tries to blow your kerbal off.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI did not used these mods KJR and WorldStabilizer. Obviously you can try to remove these mods temporary and see if problem gone.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gordon Dry","CreatedById":163177,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-02T16:26:00Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022161502\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dizor\u003C/a\u003E ofc the vessel was either floating in space or standing landed on ground.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222019-12-02T16:26:14Z\u0022 title=\u002212/02/2019 04:26  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00224 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 2, 2019\u003C/time\u003E by Gordon Dry\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whale_2","CreatedById":167015,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-02T20:53:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223712469\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575292072\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gordon Dry\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n7 hours ago, Gordon Dry said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022161502\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dizor\u003C/a\u003E \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167015-whale_2/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167015\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167015-whale_2/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@whale_2\u003C/a\u003E I will do a test next session, I just add \u003Cem\u003EKerbalEVA\u003C/em\u003E to the \u003Cem\u003EexcludePartModules\u003C/em\u003E list.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nKerbals normally are not \u0022stabilized\u0022, unless this option tweaked in config file.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Gordon Dry","CreatedById":163177,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-05T15:03:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167015-whale_2/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167015\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167015-whale_2/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@whale_2\u003C/a\u003E after doing that change the behaviour also changed. The Kerbal just stays at the ladder / hatch handle without floating \u0022down\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"whale_2","CreatedById":167015,"CreatedDateTime":"2019-12-08T18:36:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223713640\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022139024\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221575558214\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022163177\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Gordon Dry\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\nOn 12/5/2019 at 4:03 PM, Gordon Dry said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167015-whale_2/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022167015\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/167015-whale_2/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@whale_2\u003C/a\u003E after doing that change the behaviour also changed. The Kerbal just stays at the ladder / hatch handle without floating \u0022down\u0022.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nGood to now, I\u0027ll review the exclusion logic for kerbals.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Dizor","CreatedById":161502,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-10-18T19:50:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nNew version 1.10 is released.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFixed boarding seats approach to be compatible with LadderWarp mod.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Krazy1","CreatedById":203523,"CreatedDateTime":"2020-12-20T02:40:02Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi \u003Ca contenteditable=\u0022false\u0022 data-ipshover=\u0022\u0022 data-ipshover-target=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0026amp;do=hovercard\u0022 data-mentionid=\u0022161502\u0022 href=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/profile/161502-dizor/\u0022 rel=\u0022\u0022\u003E@Dizor\u003C/a\u003EThis mod looks brilliant. But I\u0027ve been using ESDF keys for 25 years, since\u00A0 DoomII.\u00A0WASD seems illogical.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nFor EVA I do: E forward, A turn left, S translate left, D back, F translate right, G turn right\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003ESo F would keep toggling auto-grab for me.\u003C/s\u003E\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EI believe\u00A0you would\u00A0never want to activate\u00A0both auto-grab and auto-board, so\u00A0couldn\u0027t you just make the B key cycle through 3 modes: auto-grab, auto-board, neither?\u00A0\u00A0\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cs\u003EOr maybe make a tiny\u00A0text config file in the gamedata\\EasyBoard folder so we can assign them how we want?\u00A0\u003C/s\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThanks\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPS I tried it... F still does normal movement for me;\u00A0not auto-grab. Auto-board works great. That\u0027s really what\u00A0I wanted anyway.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nPPS Oh... the auto-grab does work. I remapped T for \u0022use/ grab\u0022 and the default\u00A0\u00A0was F apparently.\u00A0 Everyone kept referring to the specific B and F keys instead of the functions those\u00A0keys do, so I assumed the keys were hard-coded.\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222020-12-20T05:38:00Z\u0022 title=\u002212/20/2020 05:38  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00223 yr\u0022\u003EDecember 20, 2020\u003C/time\u003E by Krazy1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"}]}